{"name":"Batteries.StdDeprecations","instances":[],"imports":["Init","Batteries.Tactic.Alias","Batteries.Data.DList.Basic","Batteries.Data.PairingHeap","Batteries.Data.BinomialHeap.Basic","Batteries.Data.HashMap.Basic","Batteries.Data.RBMap.Basic","Batteries.Data.UnionFind.Basic"],"declarations":[{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/af731107d531b39cd7278c73f91c573f40340612/Batteries/StdDeprecations.lean#L52-L52","name":"Std.UnionFind","line":52,"kind":"def","docLink":"./Batteries/StdDeprecations.html#Std.UnionFind","doc":"**Alias** of `Batteries.UnionFind`.\n\n---\n\n### Union-find data structure\n\nThe `UnionFind` structure is an implementation of disjoint-set data structure\nthat uses path compression to make the primary operations run in amortized\nnearly linear time. The nodes of a `UnionFind` structure `s` are natural\nnumbers smaller than `s.size`. The structure associates with a canonical\nrepresentative from its equivalence class. The structure can be extended\nusing the `push` operation and equivalence classes can be updated using the\n`union` operation.\n\nThe main operations for `UnionFind` are:\n\n* `empty`/`mkEmpty` are used to create a new empty structure.\n* `size` returns the size of the data structure.\n* `push` adds a new node to a structure, unlinked to any other node.\n* `union` links two nodes of the data structure, joining their equivalence\n  classes, and performs path compression.\n* `find` returns the canonical representative of a node and updates the data\n  structure using path compression.\n* `root` returns the canonical representative of a node without altering the\n  data structure.\n* `checkEquiv` checks whether two nodes have the same canonical representative\n  and updates the structure using path compression.\n\nMost use cases should prefer `find` over `root` to benefit from the speedup from path-compression.\n\nThe main operations use `Fin s.size` to represent nodes of the union-find structure.\nSome alternatives are provided:\n\n* `unionN`, `findN`, `rootN`, `checkEquivN` use `Fin n` with a proof that `n = s.size`.\n* `union!`, `find!`, `root!`, `checkEquiv!` use `Nat` and panic when the indices are out of bounds.\n* `findD`, `rootD`, `checkEquivD` use `Nat` and treat out of bound indices as isolated nodes.\n\nThe noncomputable relation `UnionFind.Equiv` is provided to use the equivalence relation from a\n`UnionFind` structure in the context of proofs.\n"},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/StdDeprecations.html#Std.UnionFind\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">UnionFind</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/af731107d531b39cd7278c73f91c573f40340612/Batteries/StdDeprecations.lean#L51-L51","name":"Std.UFNode","line":51,"kind":"def","docLink":"./Batteries/StdDeprecations.html#Std.UFNode","doc":"**Alias** of `Batteries.UFNode`.\n\n---\n\nUnion-find node type "},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/StdDeprecations.html#Std.UFNode\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">UFNode</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/af731107d531b39cd7278c73f91c573f40340612/Batteries/StdDeprecations.lean#L50-L50","name":"Std.mkBinomialHeap","line":50,"kind":"def","docLink":"./Batteries/StdDeprecations.html#Std.mkBinomialHeap","doc":"**Alias** of `Batteries.mkBinomialHeap`.\n\n---\n\n`O(1)`. Make a new empty binomial heap. "},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/StdDeprecations.html#Std.mkBinomialHeap\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">mkBinomialHeap</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(α : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(le : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">α</span> → <span class=\"fn\">α</span> → <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Batteries/Data/BinomialHeap/Basic.html#Batteries.BinomialHeap\">Batteries.BinomialHeap</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span> <span class=\"fn\">le</span></span></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/af731107d531b39cd7278c73f91c573f40340612/Batteries/StdDeprecations.lean#L49-L49","name":"Std.BinomialHeap","line":49,"kind":"def","docLink":"./Batteries/StdDeprecations.html#Std.BinomialHeap","doc":"**Alias** of `Batteries.BinomialHeap`.\n\n---\n\nA [binomial heap](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Binomial_heap) is a data structure which supports\nthe following primary operations:\n\n* `insert : α → BinomialHeap α → BinomialHeap α`: add an element to the heap\n* `deleteMin : BinomialHeap α → Option (α × BinomialHeap α)`:\n  remove the minimum element from the heap\n* `merge : BinomialHeap α → BinomialHeap α → BinomialHeap α`: combine two heaps\n\nThe first two operations are known as a \"priority queue\", so this could be called\na \"mergeable priority queue\". The standard choice for a priority queue is a binary heap,\nwhich supports `insert` and `deleteMin` in `O(log n)`, but `merge` is `O(n)`.\nWith a `BinomialHeap`, all three operations are `O(log n)`.\n"},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/StdDeprecations.html#Std.BinomialHeap\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">BinomialHeap</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(α : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(le : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">α</span> → <span class=\"fn\">α</span> → <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u</div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/af731107d531b39cd7278c73f91c573f40340612/Batteries/StdDeprecations.lean#L48-L48","name":"Std.mkRBMap","line":48,"kind":"def","docLink":"./Batteries/StdDeprecations.html#Std.mkRBMap","doc":"**Alias** of `Batteries.mkRBMap`.\n\n---\n\n`O(1)`. Construct a new empty map. "},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/StdDeprecations.html#Std.mkRBMap\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">mkRBMap</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(α : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(β : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> v)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(cmp : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">α</span> → <span class=\"fn\">α</span> → <a href=\"./Init/Data/Ord.html#Ordering\">Ordering</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Batteries/Data/RBMap/Basic.html#Batteries.RBMap\">Batteries.RBMap</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span> <span class=\"fn\">β</span> <span class=\"fn\">cmp</span></span></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/af731107d531b39cd7278c73f91c573f40340612/Batteries/StdDeprecations.lean#L47-L47","name":"Std.RBMap","line":47,"kind":"def","docLink":"./Batteries/StdDeprecations.html#Std.RBMap","doc":"**Alias** of `Batteries.RBMap`.\n\n---\n\nAn `RBMap` is a self-balancing binary search tree, used to store a key-value map.\nThe `cmp` function is the comparator that will be used for performing searches;\nit should satisfy the requirements of `TransCmp` for it to have sensible behavior.\n"},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/StdDeprecations.html#Std.RBMap\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">RBMap</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(α : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(β : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> v)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(cmp : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">α</span> → <span class=\"fn\">α</span> → <a href=\"./Init/Data/Ord.html#Ordering\">Ordering</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> (max u v)</div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/af731107d531b39cd7278c73f91c573f40340612/Batteries/StdDeprecations.lean#L46-L46","name":"Std.mkRBSet","line":46,"kind":"def","docLink":"./Batteries/StdDeprecations.html#Std.mkRBSet","doc":"**Alias** of `Batteries.mkRBSet`.\n\n---\n\n`O(1)`. Construct a new empty tree. "},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/StdDeprecations.html#Std.mkRBSet\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">mkRBSet</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(α : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(cmp : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">α</span> → <span class=\"fn\">α</span> → <a href=\"./Init/Data/Ord.html#Ordering\">Ordering</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Batteries/Data/RBMap/Basic.html#Batteries.RBSet\">Batteries.RBSet</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span> <span class=\"fn\">cmp</span></span></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/af731107d531b39cd7278c73f91c573f40340612/Batteries/StdDeprecations.lean#L45-L45","name":"Std.RBSet","line":45,"kind":"def","docLink":"./Batteries/StdDeprecations.html#Std.RBSet","doc":"**Alias** of `Batteries.RBSet`.\n\n---\n\nAn `RBSet` is a self-balancing binary search tree.\nThe `cmp` function is the comparator that will be used for performing searches;\nit should satisfy the requirements of `TransCmp` for it to have sensible behavior.\n"},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/StdDeprecations.html#Std.RBSet\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">RBSet</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(α : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(cmp : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">α</span> → <span class=\"fn\">α</span> → <a href=\"./Init/Data/Ord.html#Ordering\">Ordering</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u</div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/af731107d531b39cd7278c73f91c573f40340612/Batteries/StdDeprecations.lean#L44-L44","name":"Std.RBNode","line":44,"kind":"def","docLink":"./Batteries/StdDeprecations.html#Std.RBNode","doc":"**Alias** of `Batteries.RBNode`.\n\n---\n\nA red-black tree. (This is an internal implementation detail of the `RBSet` type,\nwhich includes the invariants of the tree.) This is a binary search tree augmented with\na \"color\" field which is either red or black for each node and used to implement\nthe re-balancing operations.\nSee: [Red–black tree](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Red%E2%80%93black_tree)\n"},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/StdDeprecations.html#Std.RBNode\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">RBNode</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(α : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u</div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/af731107d531b39cd7278c73f91c573f40340612/Batteries/StdDeprecations.lean#L43-L43","name":"Std.RBColor","line":43,"kind":"def","docLink":"./Batteries/StdDeprecations.html#Std.RBColor","doc":"**Alias** of `Batteries.RBColor`.\n\n---\n\nIn a red-black tree, every node has a color which is either \"red\" or \"black\"\n(this particular choice of colors is conventional). A nil node is considered black.\n"},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/StdDeprecations.html#Std.RBColor\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">RBColor</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/af731107d531b39cd7278c73f91c573f40340612/Batteries/StdDeprecations.lean#L41-L42","name":"Std.compareOfLessAndEq_eq_lt","line":41,"kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Batteries/StdDeprecations.html#Std.compareOfLessAndEq_eq_lt","doc":"**Alias** of `Batteries.compareOfLessAndEq_eq_lt`."},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/StdDeprecations.html#Std.compareOfLessAndEq_eq_lt\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">compareOfLessAndEq_eq_lt</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{α : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{x y : <span class=\"fn\">α</span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LT\">LT</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Decidable\">Decidable</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">x</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LT.lt\">&lt;</a> <span class=\"fn\">y</span>)</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#DecidableEq\">DecidableEq</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Ord.html#compareOfLessAndEq\">compareOfLessAndEq</a> <span class=\"fn\">x</span> <span class=\"fn\">y</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <a href=\"./Init/Data/Ord.html#Ordering.lt\">Ordering.lt</a></span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Iff\">↔</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">x</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LT.lt\">&lt;</a> <span class=\"fn\">y</span></span></span></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/af731107d531b39cd7278c73f91c573f40340612/Batteries/StdDeprecations.lean#L40-L40","name":"Std.LawfulOrd","line":40,"kind":"def","docLink":"./Batteries/StdDeprecations.html#Std.LawfulOrd","doc":"**Alias** of `Batteries.LawfulOrd`.\n\n---\n\n`LawfulOrd α` asserts that the `Ord` instance satisfies `LawfulCmp`. "},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/StdDeprecations.html#Std.LawfulOrd\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">LawfulOrd</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(α : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE\">LE</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LT\">LT</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#BEq\">BEq</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Ord.html#Ord\">Ord</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/af731107d531b39cd7278c73f91c573f40340612/Batteries/StdDeprecations.lean#L39-L39","name":"Std.LEOrd","line":39,"kind":"def","docLink":"./Batteries/StdDeprecations.html#Std.LEOrd","doc":"**Alias** of `Batteries.LEOrd`.\n\n---\n\n`LEOrd α` asserts that the `Ord` instance satisfies `LECmp`. "},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/StdDeprecations.html#Std.LEOrd\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">LEOrd</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(α : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE\">LE</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Ord.html#Ord\">Ord</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/af731107d531b39cd7278c73f91c573f40340612/Batteries/StdDeprecations.lean#L38-L38","name":"Std.LTOrd","line":38,"kind":"def","docLink":"./Batteries/StdDeprecations.html#Std.LTOrd","doc":"**Alias** of `Batteries.LTOrd`.\n\n---\n\n`LTOrd α` asserts that the `Ord` instance satisfies `LTCmp`. "},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/StdDeprecations.html#Std.LTOrd\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">LTOrd</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(α : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LT\">LT</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Ord.html#Ord\">Ord</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/af731107d531b39cd7278c73f91c573f40340612/Batteries/StdDeprecations.lean#L37-L37","name":"Std.BEqOrd","line":37,"kind":"def","docLink":"./Batteries/StdDeprecations.html#Std.BEqOrd","doc":"**Alias** of `Batteries.BEqOrd`.\n\n---\n\n`BEqOrd α` asserts that the `Ord` and `BEq` instances are coherent via `BEqCmp`. "},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/StdDeprecations.html#Std.BEqOrd\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">BEqOrd</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(α : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#BEq\">BEq</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Ord.html#Ord\">Ord</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/af731107d531b39cd7278c73f91c573f40340612/Batteries/StdDeprecations.lean#L36-L36","name":"Std.TransOrd","line":36,"kind":"def","docLink":"./Batteries/StdDeprecations.html#Std.TransOrd","doc":"**Alias** of `Batteries.TransOrd`.\n\n---\n\n`TransOrd α` asserts that the `Ord` instance satisfies `TransCmp`. "},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/StdDeprecations.html#Std.TransOrd\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">TransOrd</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(α : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Ord.html#Ord\">Ord</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/af731107d531b39cd7278c73f91c573f40340612/Batteries/StdDeprecations.lean#L35-L35","name":"Std.OrientedOrd","line":35,"kind":"def","docLink":"./Batteries/StdDeprecations.html#Std.OrientedOrd","doc":"**Alias** of `Batteries.OrientedOrd`.\n\n---\n\n`OrientedOrd α` asserts that the `Ord` instance satisfies `OrientedCmp`. "},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/StdDeprecations.html#Std.OrientedOrd\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">OrientedOrd</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(α : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Ord.html#Ord\">Ord</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/af731107d531b39cd7278c73f91c573f40340612/Batteries/StdDeprecations.lean#L34-L34","name":"Std.LawfulCmp","line":34,"kind":"def","docLink":"./Batteries/StdDeprecations.html#Std.LawfulCmp","doc":"**Alias** of `Batteries.LawfulCmp`.\n\n---\n\n`LawfulCmp cmp` asserts that the `LE`, `LT`, `BEq` instances are all coherent with each other\nand with `cmp`, describing a strict weak order (a linear order except for antisymmetry). "},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/StdDeprecations.html#Std.LawfulCmp\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">LawfulCmp</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{α : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE\">LE</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LT\">LT</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#BEq\">BEq</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(cmp : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">α</span> → <span class=\"fn\">α</span> → <a href=\"./Init/Data/Ord.html#Ordering\">Ordering</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/af731107d531b39cd7278c73f91c573f40340612/Batteries/StdDeprecations.lean#L33-L33","name":"Std.LECmp","line":33,"kind":"def","docLink":"./Batteries/StdDeprecations.html#Std.LECmp","doc":"**Alias** of `Batteries.LECmp`.\n\n---\n\n`LECmp cmp` asserts that `cmp x y ≠ .gt` and `x ≤ y` coincide. "},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/StdDeprecations.html#Std.LECmp\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">LECmp</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{α : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE\">LE</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(cmp : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">α</span> → <span class=\"fn\">α</span> → <a href=\"./Init/Data/Ord.html#Ordering\">Ordering</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/af731107d531b39cd7278c73f91c573f40340612/Batteries/StdDeprecations.lean#L32-L32","name":"Std.LTCmp","line":32,"kind":"def","docLink":"./Batteries/StdDeprecations.html#Std.LTCmp","doc":"**Alias** of `Batteries.LTCmp`.\n\n---\n\n`LTCmp cmp` asserts that `cmp x y = .lt` and `x < y` coincide. "},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/StdDeprecations.html#Std.LTCmp\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">LTCmp</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{α : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LT\">LT</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(cmp : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">α</span> → <span class=\"fn\">α</span> → <a href=\"./Init/Data/Ord.html#Ordering\">Ordering</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/af731107d531b39cd7278c73f91c573f40340612/Batteries/StdDeprecations.lean#L31-L31","name":"Std.BEqCmp","line":31,"kind":"def","docLink":"./Batteries/StdDeprecations.html#Std.BEqCmp","doc":"**Alias** of `Batteries.BEqCmp`.\n\n---\n\n`BEqCmp cmp` asserts that `cmp x y = .eq` and `x == y` coincide. "},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/StdDeprecations.html#Std.BEqCmp\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">BEqCmp</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{α : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#BEq\">BEq</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(cmp : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">α</span> → <span class=\"fn\">α</span> → <a href=\"./Init/Data/Ord.html#Ordering\">Ordering</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/af731107d531b39cd7278c73f91c573f40340612/Batteries/StdDeprecations.lean#L30-L30","name":"Std.TransCmp","line":30,"kind":"def","docLink":"./Batteries/StdDeprecations.html#Std.TransCmp","doc":"**Alias** of `Batteries.TransCmp`.\n\n---\n\n`TransCmp cmp` asserts that `cmp` induces a transitive relation. "},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/StdDeprecations.html#Std.TransCmp\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">TransCmp</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{α : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Sort</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(cmp : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">α</span> → <span class=\"fn\">α</span> → <a href=\"./Init/Data/Ord.html#Ordering\">Ordering</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/af731107d531b39cd7278c73f91c573f40340612/Batteries/StdDeprecations.lean#L29-L29","name":"Std.OrientedCmp","line":29,"kind":"def","docLink":"./Batteries/StdDeprecations.html#Std.OrientedCmp","doc":"**Alias** of `Batteries.OrientedCmp`.\n\n---\n\n`OrientedCmp cmp` asserts that `cmp` is determined by the relation `cmp x y = .lt`. "},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/StdDeprecations.html#Std.OrientedCmp\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">OrientedCmp</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{α : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Sort</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(cmp : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">α</span> → <span class=\"fn\">α</span> → <a href=\"./Init/Data/Ord.html#Ordering\">Ordering</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/af731107d531b39cd7278c73f91c573f40340612/Batteries/StdDeprecations.lean#L28-L28","name":"Std.TotalBLE","line":28,"kind":"def","docLink":"./Batteries/StdDeprecations.html#Std.TotalBLE","doc":"**Alias** of `Batteries.TotalBLE`.\n\n---\n\n`TotalBLE le` asserts that `le` has a total order, that is, `le a b ∨ le b a`. "},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/StdDeprecations.html#Std.TotalBLE\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">TotalBLE</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{α : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Sort</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(le : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">α</span> → <span class=\"fn\">α</span> → <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/af731107d531b39cd7278c73f91c573f40340612/Batteries/StdDeprecations.lean#L27-L27","name":"Std.PairingHeapImp.Heap","line":27,"kind":"def","docLink":"./Batteries/StdDeprecations.html#Std.PairingHeapImp.Heap","doc":"**Alias** of `Batteries.PairingHeapImp.Heap`.\n\n---\n\nA `Heap` is the nodes of the pairing heap.\nEach node have two pointers: `child` going to the first child of this node,\nand `sibling` goes to the next sibling of this tree.\nSo it actually encodes a forest where each node has children\n`node.child`, `node.child.sibling`, `node.child.sibling.sibling`, etc.\n\nEach edge in this forest denotes a `le a b` relation that has been checked, so\nthe root is smaller than everything else under it.\n"},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/StdDeprecations.html#Std.PairingHeapImp.Heap\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">PairingHeapImp</span>.<span class=\"name\">Heap</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(α : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u</div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/af731107d531b39cd7278c73f91c573f40340612/Batteries/StdDeprecations.lean#L26-L26","name":"Std.DList","line":26,"kind":"def","docLink":"./Batteries/StdDeprecations.html#Std.DList","doc":"**Alias** of `Batteries.DList`.\n\n---\n\nA difference List is a Function that, given a List, returns the original\ncontents of the difference List prepended to the given List.\nThis structure supports `O(1)` `append` and `push` operations on lists, making it\nuseful for append-heavy uses such as logging and pretty printing.\n"},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/StdDeprecations.html#Std.DList\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">DList</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(α : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u</div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/af731107d531b39cd7278c73f91c573f40340612/Batteries/StdDeprecations.lean#L25-L25","name":"Std.mkHashMap","line":25,"kind":"def","docLink":"./Batteries/StdDeprecations.html#Std.mkHashMap","doc":"**Alias** of `Batteries.mkHashMap`.\n\n---\n\nMake a new hash map with the specified capacity. "},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/StdDeprecations.html#Std.mkHashMap\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">mkHashMap</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{α : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{β : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#BEq\">BEq</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Hashable\">Hashable</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(capacity : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a> := <span class=\"fn\">0</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Batteries/Data/HashMap/Basic.html#Batteries.HashMap\">Batteries.HashMap</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span> <span class=\"fn\">β</span></span></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/af731107d531b39cd7278c73f91c573f40340612/Batteries/StdDeprecations.lean#L24-L24","name":"Std.AssocList","line":24,"kind":"def","docLink":"./Batteries/StdDeprecations.html#Std.AssocList","doc":"**Alias** of `Batteries.AssocList`.\n\n---\n\n`AssocList α β` is \"the same as\" `List (α × β)`, but flattening the structure\nleads to one fewer pointer indirection (in the current code generator).\nIt is mainly intended as a component of `HashMap`, but it can also be used as a plain\nkey-value map.\n"},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/StdDeprecations.html#Std.AssocList\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">AssocList</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(α : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(β : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> v)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> (max u v)</div></div>"}]}